---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { CONTACT_EMAIL } from '../consts';
import { withBase } from '../utils';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About this archive.">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>
      Some things are worth keeping. Not because they're yours, but because they
      once changed the temperature of a room you were standing in, and you wanted
      to keep standing there.
    </p>
    <p>
      There are three ways in.
      <a class="section-link" href={withBase('/look')}>Look</a> is for images,
      kept for the way they hold light or hold still.
      <a class="section-link" href={withBase('/read')}>Read</a> is for words worth
      carrying around.
      <a class="section-link" href={withBase('/act')}>Act</a> is for the small
      rules worth living by.
    </p>
    <p>
      Most of the images aren't mine. Where I know the source, it's credited.
      Where I don't, I'd like to; if you recognise something, tell me and I'll add
      the credit or take it down.
    </p>
    {CONTACT_EMAIL && (
      <p><a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a></p>
    )}
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Subtle underline that links each section word to its page. */
  .section-link {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-rule);
    transition: text-decoration-color 0.18s ease;
  }
  .section-link:hover {
    text-decoration-color: currentColor;
  }
</style>
